cardano_node_tests.utils.logfiles.add_ignore_rule(*, files_glob: str, regex: str, ignore_file_id: str, skip_after: float = 0.0) → None[source]ÔÉÅ

Add ignore rule for expected errors.

Parameters:

  • files_glob ‚Äì A glob matching files that the regex should apply to.

  • regex ‚Äì A regex that should be ignored.

  • ignore_file_id ‚Äì

    The id of a ignore file the ignore rule will be added to.

    NOTE: When ignore_file_id matches pytest-xdist worker id (the worker_id fixture), the rule will be deleted during the test teardown.

  • skip_after ‚Äì

    The time in seconds after which the rule will expire. This is to avoid reporting the ignored errors in subsequent tests. It can take several seconds for the errors to appear in log files and we don‚Äôt want to wait for them after each test.

    NOTE: The rule will expire only when there are no yet to be searched log messages that were created before the skip_after time.
